caption: Oh, wow. If you haven’t tried this place, get her now. You are missing out.
Ok place for delicious soup. Really nothing but great experiences here, so I will be back. They have a lot of positive reviews for a reason.
Soup, mmm, my favorite treat. good place to catch up with friends. the staff was very sociable and kind. this place has a good atmosphere.
Nice place to have soups of variety
i felt like it wasnt worth over $15

First time trying and was disappointed on the service. I ordered the cheddar broccoli and got some tomato bisque soup. Also ordered a cranberry almond Sonoma salad and they put blue cheese on it. On the menu it didn't say it came with bleu cheese. And lastly they have me the option of white or multi grain bread and I was given white. I'm willing to give them a second chance because the tomato bisque soup was good but I didn't touch the salad because I can't stand even a little bleu cheese. But management needs to do something about this and their dirty tables that seemed like they only get cleaned once a day
Soup, yeah, excellent. Got there near six, it wasn't packed at all. Bring your hunger - portions are filling.
(Translated by Google) Food was super good, great staff and amazing manager.  (Original) La comida era súper buena, excelente personal y gerente increíble.
Excellent spot for delicious Soup. The prices are well within reason for the quality. Mood here is similar to Fresno's scene.
French onion soup is great.

The Mac and Soup/Salad/Sandwich and bread (multigrain or french bread) are consistently fresh, properly prepared and a great value for the price.  Staff — Customer Service Focus with a Smile...  Definitely recommend it.   Also, the manager, She is ever present to provide whatever your needs and/or like(s) from their menu for special orders (small or large).   Thank You!!!  — Anton Jones
Make sure you have everything you need before you go. Food is good, but staff do not remember utensils, napkins, beverages, etc
Consistently good soup and a semi-rotating menu to keep it interesting.
My favorite lunch spot
Dated interior, standard out of the can soups and flavor.

The soup was delicious and the staff reasonably helpful.  The seating area was not well kept, though.  Discarded items lay on the floor and a stained carpet made it less than appealing.   I may return when I'm next in the area, but will likely get my meal to go.
Very good soup selection and a cozy spot to just take a breath in the middle of downtown.  Could be cleaner.
White bean and Turkey sausage was pretty good
Good is pretty good

Zoup! was zelicious!! I'll be back!! They have 12 smoky cauldrons filled with a myriad of tasty soup combinations (chicken pot pie soup, white bean and turkey sausage,  chicken tortilla, etc.).  And they ENCOURAGE you to sample the soups!!! Additionally they have bread bowls kicked up a notch with yummy flavors and cheeses.  To add to this zoupa-licious party, you can select a salad and/or sandwich (on multigrain or french bread). Can't decide? No problem, Zoup allows you match two, to create your own combo!! I'm all Zouped up!!!

Was on my way to Union Station and noticed Zoup. Went in just as they opened at 11:00. Got a sample of their Seafood Soup and liked it and ordered it. I was able to get whole wheat bread with it. The Seafood soup was excellent. What I liked was the variety of soups to choose from. Staff were friendly even though they were very busy putting up on line orders. Will definitely stop again.

Absolutely delicious pizza! The crust, sauce, and toppings were amazing! We did extra pepperoni's, jalapeños, and basil. We also ordered a large Cesar salad with pepperoni on it, we were a party of three and there was plenty for each of us.Wish there was a Grimaldi's in SD!!
This place has a really good customer service as well as food they serve. The bread was fresh and crispy and the soup was beyond delicious. Definitely recommend!
More soup please!

I used to love this place, however a lot has changed. The bread is dry and hard, not warmed. They no longer offer certain items for their salads, and the raspberry vinaigrette seems to have changed. My salad seemed thrown together with a ton of craisins. I was very disappointed with this purchase. Also I noticed they were not crowded at all.
A great light lunch!

These soups always hit the spot, especially on gloomy days. The rolls are always hot and fresh. They have vegan and vegetarian options as well. If you're not sure what to get, they let you sample them. If you're going on a lunch break, there is usually a long wait time. The lines can be long during lunch hour.
The chicken tortilla soup was the right amount of spicy and the Turkey & Bacon Club was good.
I love all the options they have for the daily soup
Lobster bisque 🤤🤤

My co-woker and I went there for lunch and the food was horrible.  The whiten chicken chili was sweet and nasty.  I ordered a veggie wrap that should've been labeled a cold shredded carrot wrap.  It was sloppy and nasty.
Wasn't what I expectedbut not bad
The bathroom is out of soap, out of two soups, the service team seems out of it, and they are out of bread.
Best (and loudest!) Soup in town. Get ready to get honeyed by staff.
Always a lot of selection and delicious!
Excellent place for a quick bowl of soup and a sandwich!
great choices of soups and really tasty sandwiches  Update 4 years later: still really good soups, didn't have a sandwich this time so I can't speak to those
Absolutely love their bread boules
Roasted garlic chicken kale soup. All I gotta say.

You walk in, a little confusing on where to go. You figure it out, the person behind the counter asks you what do you want to taste. You reply nothing, I'm ready to order, do you step down to the the register, yes. Soup is okay. Service is adequate. Prices are okay.
Great service and the soup is delicious.
Visited the location in Woodridge today, first timer, service was wonderful and food was amazing.

How sad! They are not open evenings any more. We've stopped here around 6 PM maybe 50 times over the past few years, on our way to some event downtown, and loved their tasty and inexpensive food, and the friendly and comfortable atmosphere. But yesterday they were CLOSED - new hours. There is a place right next door but it's disgustingly loud, and there is also a place a block east that's nice but much more expensive.
Great food!!
You'd love it
A lot of good tasting soup that you can try. This was one of our go-to places for lunch!
Very small selection of salad options. The staff was also very rough and not very friendly. Fast service and cheap prices though.

(Translated by Google) Highly recommended if you want to warm up with a hot soup. The lady who attended us was very friendly and attentive. Very well priced and fast!  (Original) Muy recomendable si quieres entrar en calor con una sopa caliente. La señora que nos atendió fue muy amable y atenta. Muy bien de precio y rápidos!
My favorite lunch spot in the loop.  Great prices, and the soup selection is varied, changing, and delicious.  I highly recommend ordering via the Ritual app as well to save time on waiting in line!

Features a rotating selection of soups, including some vegetarian options.  There is also a decent selection of salads and sandwiches. Wish they were open on weekends!  Food is usually prepared quickly, though not surprisingly the place can get busy during the lunch hour.
Great soups
My favorite place! Great staff! Keep up the great job guys!
$11+ for a half soup and sandwich.. Ridiculous. The loaded potatoe soup was not good, I have had WAYY better. Friendly staff at least
Food was really good.  Lines were long but worth wait.
People are so nice.
Loved the freshly made soups... try crab n rice soup...tooo good
Staff is not courteous. It took 3 employees to pass a bag of prepaid food over the counter.  The soup itself (pot pie) not as good as Potbellys.
Friendly Clean Quick  Ate: Lobster Bisque (cup)
Good fresh sandwiches
The best chicken pot pie soup!!! Yum!!
Fast, organized and polite. Gets busy, but they handle it well.

I usually go here for lunch during the workweek.  The soups and sandwiches are always delicious and are not unreasonably priced.  The place does have a tendency to get very crowded during lunch times, so I highly recommend ordering ahead online for pick-up and skipping the line.
The soup is good, and the customer service is OK
Better quality than Panera.
Zoup is one of my favorite places when it's cold out. Pretty much all of the soups and sandwiches are great ways to warm up when the weather outside is frightful.
The clam chowder was perfect!
The way their line is set up is kinda dumb, but the soup is really good.
Love the variety of options you get here.
I've been going to Zoup on Adams for quite awhile now; however, my last few visits it has been a disappointment with wrong orders. Great food and service but need to pay attention to orders
Awesome
The service was OK, but the soup was terrible.
Always good soup and they let you sample first.
Fairly fast and free samples of the soups of the day.
Awful. $13 for cold goopy soup and a salad that they gave me enough dressing to dress 3 leaves of lettuce.
Amazing!!! The lobster bisque melts in your mouth and the chicken pot pie soup is so yummy!!! I love this place.
Great soup spot.  Highly recommend the lobster bisque!
The food was fast and hot when delivered. First time eating here. Easy on the pocket, good serving sizes, and hearty. This is a healthy comfort food spot for cold weather.
Numerous soup selections. Good luck getting a seat if you're eating here during the weekday lunch. Order ahead of time for pickup to avoid the wait times.

I LOVE this place. Since this location is right across the street from my job, I have lunch here at least 3 times a week and the food is amazing every time. I normally get the choose two option. On a normal day I get a sandwich and soup, but when I am very hungry I get a salad and a sandwich, and still hardly ever finish everything. The salad is very filling. The staff is very friendly. I order online because their line can get very long during my lunch time at noon. I have never had any issues with my food not being ready when I order online. Everything I order is always freshly made by the time I pick up. You get to customize your meal, when you order online, and if you are a picky eater like myself, then this comes in very handy. I think the price is actually pretty reasonable, considering the portion sizes, especially if you select the try two option. If I see a new soup on their online menu for the day, then I wait in line and try it. You get to try as many soups as you like. Highly recommend this place.
It was very good. Food was fast and was delicious. Although.... The water pressure on the fountain machine was very low

On one of the coldest days of the year, on a day that chills you to the bone, and from sitting around checking out Zoup! It definitely stands tall. As I'd watched people eagerly enter to the sampling right away with a variety of good close to as home-made soup as it gets. I had the Roadhouse Silron Chili, which they ordered out of really fast.(Quickly replaced by the Turkey Chili...interesting) I double with the chili for $1 more and got Tomato Vegetables. Both great. As I sit here satisfied I am asking do I have room for one more....?

My coworkers all seem to love Zoup, and after working in the Loop for about a year and a half, I figured I'd give this place a try. I was recommended to try the lobster bisque, so that's what I was planning on ordering. I was happy to find out that they offer free samples, and tried the lobster bisque and the seafood chowder. I actually didn't think the lobster bisque was that good, but really enjoyed the seafood chowder, and went with that instead. I made it a combo and got the chicken Greek wrap. Ehhh pass on the chicken Greek wrap--- I felt like I could have made something better at home-- it was just really bland tasting. Maybe their actual sandwiches on bread are better... especially since the sourdough bread that came with the soup were good.  At least the food comes out pretty quickly, and there's plenty of spots to sit at during lunch.

Hearty and delicious soups, refreshing sandwiches. If I had to fault one thing, it would be value. Prices are not exorbitant, but it is just soup and sandwiches after all, yet hard to get a sufficient meal for under $9.
I've tried a few of their soups and they were all tasty and interesting.  I love the idea of a soup restaurant.  It's always really crowded around lunch, but the line moves pretty quickly.

Very nice place for lunch. Apart from interesting varieties of soups they also have salads and sandwiches. Place is clean and wasn't too busy after 1pm. Recommend for lunch! Easiest way to find it: its in front of the postal office.

On a cold day in Chiberia, what is better the. Some hot soup?  Nothing!  This is a great place for a quick lunch. You come up to the counter thinking you are about to order but it is really just the sample section so you have an easier (or harder) time deciding what you want.  My service was quick and the food was hot and delicious. Expensive? Not really for a place in the loop. Wrong order review? They print a label on top of your Zoup with your name and what you ordered. Not sure how the order was mixed up but people to make errors time to time. Hope they fixed it if they.
Best Lobster Bisque at a lunch spot in the loop.

OMG! I love the new Zoup in the Loop!! I LOVE soup and this was like my heaven! The best thing about this place is that they allow you to taste the 12 different kinds of soup but the downside, is that everyone wants to taste, and they guys giving out samples are also the guys filling soup orders, so it could take a while of waiting at the soup bins.  The reason why everyone will sample the soup is because they change up their selections daily. And the selections can be pretty interesting. I tasted the pumpkin pie bisque which was too sweet, and the cheeseburger bisque, which was too salty, and the turkey chili, which was just right.  I could make a whole meal out of soup, but for those that can't, there's also salads and sandwiches on the menu.
